        "product_attribute_type_id"=>62,
        "product_attribute_value"=>"[{\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/www.billboard.com\\/articles\\/news\\/6612949\\/yes-chris-squire-appreciation\",\"id\":\"1ea1f02a6e76a45e33c83b69e9b378b0\",\"date_found\":\"2015-06-29T00:00:00\",\"name\":\"Yes Bassist Chris Squire: An Appreciation\",\"summary\":\"other musicians at the time, we really wanted to push the boundaries and explore and not feel held in check by conventional rock 'n' roll rules,\\\" former singer Anderson recalls. \\\"We were quite determined to be original.\\\" Yes followed the lead of the Moody Blues, <span>Pink Floyd<\\/span>, Procol Harum and, of course, the Beatles post-Sgt. Pepper's Lonely Hearts Club Band, fusing melodic pop conventions with advanced compositional ambitions. While the group's first two albums explored advanced forms of pop, lengthy, suite-like songs such as \\\"Roundabout,\\\" \\\"Starship Trooper,\\\" \\\"Yours Is No Disgrace\\\" and\"},{\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/www.jambase.com\\/Articles\\/125583\\/Kung-Fu-Drummer-Adrian-Tramontano-Sits-In-With-PTF\",\"id\":\"15adca83db6377cef6c8e435cb0b1d1d\",\"date_found\":\"2015-06-27T00:00:00\",\"name\":\"Kung Fu Drummer Adrian Tramontano Sits-In With PTF\",\"summary\":\"Phish\\/<span>Pink Floyd<\\/span>\\/Talking Heads tribute act Pink Talking Fish brought their tour to The Northeast Fair in Pittston, Pennsylvania for a two-set headlining show last night. Making for a special evening of cover tunes, Kung Fu drummer Adrian Tramontano joined the tribute band for their entire performance. [Photo by Photo By Andrew Blackstein] The first set included a segment of seques featuring all three bands PTF covers via a performance of \\\"Wilson\\\" > \\\"Young Lust\\\" > \\\"Wilson\\\" > \\\"Nothing But Flower.\\\" The second set featured a \\\"Crosseyed & Painless\\\" opener followed by a \\\"Mike's Groove\\\" that included\"},{\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/www.jambands.com\\/news\\/2015\\/06\\/26\\/kung-fu-drummer-plays-with-pink-talking-fish\",\"id\":\"f22f2adc912aaf3d155b51380b427a0c\",\"date_found\":\"2015-06-27T00:00:00\",\"name\":\"Kung Fu Drummer Plays with Pink Talking Fish\",\"summary\":\"Last night in Pittston, PA, Pink Talking Fish welcomed out Kung Fu drummer Adrian Tramontano for the entire two set show at the Northeast Fair. Among the tunes played were an opening \\\"2001\\\" jam as well as Phish tunes \\\"Wilson\\\" and \\\"Run Like an Antelope.\\\" <span>The Pink Floyd<\\/span> catalog was also well-represented with takes on \\\"Have a Cigar,\\\" \\\"Young Lust,\\\" \\\"Wish You Were Here,\\\" \\\"Another Brick in the Wall\\\" and others. As always, PTF shared a fair amount of Talking Heads material. Among them, \\\"Life During Wartime,\\\" \\\"Burning Down the House,\\\" \\\"Crosseyed and Painless\\\" and more. Next up for Pink Talking Fish is a Mike\"},{\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/www.antimusic.com\\/news\\/15\\/June\\/25Pink_Floyd,_King_Crimson_Lead_Progressive_Music_Awards_Nominations.shtml\",\"id\":\"7f18b6a3335bd484e87fcf982a3c6ad9\",\"date_found\":\"2015-06-25T00:00:00\",\"name\":\"Pink Floyd, King Crimson Lead Progressive Music Awards Nominations\",\"summary\":\"Awards. The 2015 awards will again take place at London's Underglobe venue, beneath Shakepseare's Globe Theatre, on Thursday September 3. This year, the event will be hosted of the first time by TV presenter Matthew Wright. You can vote for your choice of the nominees at: progmagazine.com\\/awards. <span>Pink Floyd<\\/span>'s The Endless River album sees them pick up three nominations for Grand Design, Album and Band\\/Artist of the Year. King Crimson and Steven Wilson are the only other artists with three nominations and go head-to-head in the Grand Design category. Wilson is also nominated for Band\\/Artist of the ... Steve Hillage for the first time. I spent a lot of time listening to his Green album and his stuff with Gong but I never thought I'd meet him. I also met Robert John Godfrey, who I'd seen live many times but had never met before. The experience was only marred by the fact I had to get up at 4am the next morning to do my show, so I think I might take the Friday off this time!\\\" See the full nomination list here. Classic Rock Magazine is an official news provider for antiMusic.com. Copyright Classic Rock Magazine- Excerpted here with permission. <span>Pink Floyd<\\/span>, King Crimson Lead Progressive Music Awards Nominations\"},{\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/www.billboard.com\\/articles\\/news\\/dance\\/6605919\\/nicolas-jaar-drops-surprise-album-pomegranates\",\"id\":\"58f1407ae376ea8ee3bc513dff4daa17\",\"date_found\":\"2015-06-25T00:00:00\",\"name\":\"Nicolas Jaar Drops Surprise Album 'Pomegranates'\",\"summary\":\"meandering and memorable debut Space is Only Noise in 2011, the Chilean-American talent has managed to avoid putting out a solo successor.Indie Beat: Nicolas Jaar on Building a Label for Digital Natives His DARKSIDE project with Dave Harrington was a different (yet just as worthwhile) beast that channeled <span>Pink Floyd<\\/span> in its majestic rock-oriented arrangements. The release of Jaar's third EP Nymphs II in May followed the revelation that he had composed a soundtrack to a 1969 Soviet art film called The Colour of Pomegranates. Now that soundtrack has surfaced in the form of a second standalone album titled\"},{\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/www.virginmedia.com\\/music\\/news\\/story\\/2015\\/06\\/25\\/pink-floyd-up-for-three\\/\",\"id\":\"93f95aac334de2d061d0f4b8e8c2ffb9\",\"date_found\":\"2015-06-25T00:00:00\",\"name\":\"Pink Floyd up for three Progressive Music Awards\",\"summary\":\"<span>Pink Floyd<\\/span>'s Nick Mason <span>Pink Floyd<\\/span> have been nominated for three awards at the 2015 Progressive Music Awards. The legendary rock band's chart-topping 'The Endless River' LP sees them up for the Grand Design, Best Album and Best Band\\/Artist of the Year prizes. <span>Pink Floyd<\\/span> - Dave Gilmour and Nick Mason - are joined on three nominations by King Crimson and Steven Wilson. Meanwhile, Kate Bush is up for two awards, Best Live Event and Artist of the Year, following her return to the stage in 2014, her first live shows in 35 years. The 4th Annual Progressive Music Awards - created by Prog Magazine - will take ... Summer Now (from Scorch) Vennart - Operate (from The Demon Joke) Von Hertzen Brothers - Hold Me Up (from New Day Rising) Album of the Year: Amplifier - Mystoria Beardfish - +4626 comfortzone Flying Colors - Second Nature Nightwish - Endless Forms Most Beautiful Opeth - Pale Communion <span>Pink Floyd<\\/span> - The Endless River Periphery - Juggernaut Steven Wilson - Hand.Cannot.Erase. Sweet Billy Pilgrim - Motorcade Amnesiacs The Pineapple Thief - Magnolia Band\\/Artist of the Year: Between The Buried & Me Flying Colors Kate Bush King Crimson Opeth <span>Pink Floyd<\\/span> Steve Hackett Steven Wilson Threshold Von Hertzen Brothers\"},{\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/www.jambase.com\\/Articles\\/125559\\/RecommNeds-Truls-Morck-and-Les-Big-Byrd\",\"id\":\"42cb5d3a2eb6ed60248dbbd70e290568\",\"date_found\":\"2015-06-25T00:00:00\",\"name\":\"RecommNeds | Truls Morck & Les Big Byrd\",\"summary\":\"the next couple weeks with moreextended stays in some overseas locales. This week brings us two bands from Sweden. Truls M\\u00f6rck: Truls M\\u00f6rck Truls M\\u00f6rck is an on-again\\/off-again member of heavy metal band Graveyard, buthis solo, self-titled debut album is another kind of 1970s throwback, with <span>Pink Floyd<\\/span> space-outs in an almost Laurel Canyon setting. With excellent songs and a laid-back, let-loosegroove, M\\u00f6rck comes off like a Swedish Jonathan Wilson, which is to say the album is quitegood: interstellar guitars and pre-disco electric piano and organ. It's a slow burner that'sworth a little\"},{\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/www.virginmedia.com\\/music\\/news\\/story\\/2015\\/06\\/19\\/roger-waters-told-to-hoot\\/\",\"id\":\"f216e50fab4356086b35e420c097e66b\",\"date_found\":\"2015-06-20T00:00:00\",\"name\":\"Roger Waters told to 'shoot himself'\",\"summary\":\"Roger Waters Roger Waters was told to ''shoot himself'' by his school teacher as a child. <span>The Pink Floyd<\\/span> musician revealed his tutor confronted him in class as a youngster and told him he would never do anything valuable with his life because he was ''useless''. He recalled: ''I've had some measure of success and there's no question that it provides one with something of a bulwark against T.E House who was the a*shole at my grammar school who told me I was a complete f**king idiot. ''He was an English teacher and he was my form master when I was 13. ''He said I would never become anything and might as well\"},{\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/music-news.com\\/shownews.asp?H=Ed-Sheeran,-Sam-Smith-and-George-Ezra-driving-British-male-success&nItemID=90082\",\"id\":\"b118b34e11f521936a8c6882c3fe4319\",\"date_found\":\"2015-06-15T00:00:00\",\"name\":\"Ed Sheeran, Sam Smith and George Ezra driving British male success\",\"summary\":\"with Paolo Nutini and Olly Murs also performing strongly. It's a trend underlined by the recent successes of James Bay (2015), Sam Smith (2014) and Tom Odell (2013) in claiming the BRITs Critics' Choice Award following five years of Female Artist dominance. Male Groups, which last year included iconic Rock act <span>Pink Floyd<\\/span>, nevertheless accounted for a further four titles in the top 10 and also claimed over a third of sales in 2014. When each gender group's sales are analysed by nationality the UK achieved its strongest sales share (63.4 per cent) in the Male Group category and its weakest (39.3 per cent) ... Coldplay Ghost Stories Parlophone\\/Parlophone (Warner Music UK) 6. Paloma Faith A Perfect Contradiction RCA\\/RCA Label Group (Sony Music Entertainment UK) 7. One Direction Four Syco Music\\/Syco Music (Sony Music Entertainment UK) 8. Olly Murs Never Been Better Epic\\/RCA Label Group (Sony Music Entertainment UK) 9. <span>Pink Floyd<\\/span> The Endless River Rhino\\/Rhino (Warner Music UK) 10. Take That III Polydor\\/Polydor Records (Universal Music UK) Have Your Say Get our free BREAKING NEWS email for Music News and Film News. Subscribe to our YouTube channel, Twitter and NEW Intagram page. Ed Sheeran, Sam Smith and\"},{\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/music-news.com\\/shownews.asp?H=Duran-Duran-and-Kasabian-Silver-Clef-winners&nItemID=90015\",\"id\":\"313c039d07de4f1dd7ffbe81024177dc\",\"date_found\":\"2015-06-12T00:00:00\",\"name\":\"Duran Duran & Kasabian Silver Clef winners\",\"summary\":\"than \\u00a38.5 million to fund Nordoff Robbins' music therapy work. In the 40 year history of the O2 Silver Clef Lunch, there have been a total of 163 award winners. Some of the biggest names in the music industry have been honoured including David Bowie, Eric Clapton, <span>Pink Floyd<\\/span>, The Rolling Stones, Sir Paul McCartney, Sir Elton John, The Bee Gees, Michael Buble, Kylie Minogue, Pharrell Williams and many many more. #O2SilverClefs40 #MusicIsMedicine www.nordoff-robbins.org.uk Have Your Say Get our free BREAKING NEWS email for Music News and Film News. Subscribe to our YouTube channel, Twitter and NEW\"},{\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/www.jambands.com\\/news\\/2015\\/06\\/10\\/david-gilmour-plans-to-tour-north-america-in-2016\",\"id\":\"fb39d70213c1dfb4661d635b2c400c53\",\"date_found\":\"2015-06-11T00:00:00\",\"name\":\"David Gilmour Plans to Tour North America in 2016\",\"summary\":\"David Gilmour plans to tour North America in 2016. Consequence of Sound reports that <span>the Pink Floyd<\\/span> guitarist revealed the news during a Q&A session at the Borris House Festival of Writing and Ideas in Carlow, Ireland last weekend. The publication has pointed out that someone from the monthly <span>Pink Floyd<\\/span> fan podcast Brain Damage attended the event, where Gilmour revealed that he plans to hit the road on this side of the pond next year. Gilmour also shared a few more pieces of information during his appearance at the festival, including the name of his highly anticipated solo album, and performed\"},{\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/www.billboard.com\\/articles\\/news\\/6590831\\/emmylou-harris-and-dame-evelyn-glennie-honored-with-swedens-polar-music-prize\",\"id\":\"f7de379f68e91fe4212f7a66a37f5f87\",\"date_found\":\"2015-06-10T00:00:00\",\"name\":\"Emmylou Harris and Dame Evelyn Glennie Honored with Sweden's Polar Music Prize\",\"summary\":\"many of ABBA's early hits. The prize was first presented in 1992. Anderson died in 1997; his family has taken up the mantle. The long list of previous Laureates includes Paul McCartney, Elton John, B.B. King, Joni Mitchell, Ren\\u00e9e Fleming, Stevie Wonder, Ennio Morricone, Bob Dylan, <span>Pink Floyd<\\/span>, Isaac Stern, Bj\\u00f6rk, Led Zeppelin, Miriam Makeba, Patti Smith, Yo-Yo Ma, Ravi Shankar, Quincy Jones, Dizzy Gillespie, Burt Bacharach and Bruce Springsteen. Springsteen and his wife, Patti Scialfa, sent a video message to Harris: Emmylou Harris and Dame Evelyn Glennie Honored with Sweden's Polar Music Prize\"},{\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/www.jambands.com\\/news\\/2015\\/06\\/08\\/pink-talking-fish-to-play-animals-and-gamehendge-during-halloween-run\",\"id\":\"42ba649ca53364962a27b28fc0afbe22\",\"date_found\":\"2015-06-09T00:00:00\",\"name\":\"Pink Talking Fish to Play Animals and Gamehendge During Halloween Run\",\"summary\":\"Pink Talking Fish's two-night run at The Middle East in Cambridge, MA will see the band deliver a pair of unique performances as they will take on <span>Pink Floyd<\\/span>'s Animals on October 30 along with \\\"various animal oriented themes included in the song catalogues of <span>Pink Floyd<\\/span>, the Talking Heads and Phish.\\\" Halloween night will be Gamehendge-themed. The band will perform the well-known Trey Anastasio rock opera along with material from the Talking Heads and <span>Floyd<\\/span>. The Middle East will be transformed into a jungle over the two nights and attendees are encouraged to dress up as creatures of the wild. All\"},{\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/www.antimusic.com\\/news\\/15\\/June\\/09Muse_Discuss_New_Concept_Album_Drones_.shtml\",\"id\":\"eb35b48cfa4d4b5b878410697647b8ee\",\"date_found\":\"2015-06-09T00:00:00\",\"name\":\"Muse Discuss New Concept Album 'Drones'\",\"summary\":\"becomes brainwashed by the military thereby becoming a drone, but eventually fights to free himself from the mental shackles in songs like \\\"Revolt\\\" and \\\"Defector.\\\" The album comes to a head with the whopping 10-minute track \\\"Globalist,\\\" about a dictator who starts World War III as a means to find love. When compared to <span>Pink Floyd<\\/span>'s The Wall, Howard smiles and admits, \\\"I suppose the album is a bit of a concept album, yeah. It's probably the most conceptual album that we've done.\\\" The band has tried their hand at weaving story lines though a few tracks here or there, but as for Drones Howard says, \\\"It has a narrative,\"},{\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/music-news.com\\/shownews.asp?H=Roger-Waters-The-Wall-comes-to-cinemas&nItemID=89954\",\"id\":\"d80d8ba398b82047d2372612d9f144e8\",\"date_found\":\"2015-06-09T00:00:00\",\"name\":\"Roger Waters The Wall comes to cinemas\",\"summary\":\"Printable version Roger Waters, the creative genius behind musical pioneers <span>Pink Floyd<\\/span>, in association with Picturehouse Entertainment and Fathom Events, is set to bring his groundbreaking masterpiece, Roger Waters The Wall, to cinemas across the globe on Tuesday September 29. The release will hit screens across the globe at 8pm local time. Tickets go on sale on Friday 19 June and are available at www.rogerwatersthewall.com. 'The Wall Live' - the biggest worldwide tour by any solo artist in history - now comes to cinemas as a groundbreaking concert film, written and directed by Roger Waters and Sean Evans. Described by critics as \\\"nothing short of breath-taking\\\" and \\\"visually magnificent,\\\" Roger Waters The Wall had its premiere at last year's Toronto Film Festival. The film unfolds on many levels ' as an immersive concert experience of the classic <span>Pink Floyd<\\/span> album, a road movie of Waters' reckoning with the past and as a stirring anti-war film, highlighting the human cost of conflict. The event on Tuesday September 29 also features The Simple Facts; an exclusive in-conversation with Roger Waters and Nick Mason, where <span>the Pink Floyd<\\/span> rhythm section will reunite over the breaking\"}]"
